[{'text': "Xbox doesn't rhyme with Portugal", 'start': 1.069, 'duration': 3.803}, {'text': '3 years ago, in 2008, I worked during the month of 
 December as a promoter of Xbox 360 in Portugal.', 'start': 5.539, 'duration': 6.84}, {'text': 'The promotional campaign was centered on the karaoke game Lips', 'start': 13.146, 'duration': 2.77}, {'text': 'and its main goal was, above all,', 'start': 16.417, 'duration': 1.768}, {'text': 'to bring to the Xbox some of the party games 
 that were so successful to the Playstation brand.', 'start': 18.185, 'duration': 4.371}, {'text': "One of the shortcomings of Microsoft's karaoke game was the lack of Portuguese music,", 'start': 23.057, 'duration': 4.771}, {'text': 'and as you may guess, it was not easy 
 to advertise a game under these circumstances,', 'start': 28.262, 'duration': 4.704}, {'text': 'even more so when the competition had an 
 extensive catalog of music, including Portuguese bands.', 'start': 33.1, 'duration': 6.173}, {'text': 'At the time, promoters were instructed to respond 
 to anyone who asked for Portuguese music', 'start': 40.04, 'duration': 4.838}, {'text': 'that they would soon arrive.', 'start': 44.945, 'duration': 1.836}, {'text': 'Today, more than one hundred songs were gradually added to the Lips catalog,', 'start': 48.215, 'duration': 4.772}, {'text': 'without the release of any Portuguese music.', 'start': 53.02, 'duration': 3.704}, {'text': "For that reason, here's my first question:", 'start': 57.124, 'duration': 3.637}, {'text': "Why didn't they release any Portuguese songs for Lips?", 'start': 60.761, 'duration': 3.136}, {'text': 'In December 2009, Microsoft Portugal announced a partnership with Vodafone', 'start': 65.198, 'duration': 4.839}, {'text': 'to include “Vodafone Casa TV” (subscription TV service) on Xbox 360.', 'start': 70.404, 'duration': 4.704}, {'text': 'This integration allowed users of both platforms', 'start': 75.108, 'duration': 3.938}, {'text': ' to see pay-per view television channels in the 
 console, using it as a traditional set-top box.', 'start': 79.046, 'duration': 4.671}, {'text': 'Although this type of functionality was perceived as very interesting,', 'start': 84.285, 'duration': 3.103}, {'text': 'it was frustrating to see Microsoft making a partnership with a TV 
 service that is absent from the majority of Portuguese homes.', 'start': 87.421, 'duration': 5.906}, {'text': 'It turns out that Vodafone had, at the time of 
 this partnership, 0.3% of pay-TV market in Portugal,', 'start': 93.66, 'duration': 6.206}, {'text': 'or if we look at the absolute numbers: about 
 7,800 subscribers, according to data from ANACOM.', 'start': 100.334, 'duration': 5.936}, {'text': 'On the other hand - and for the very same December of 2009 -', 'start': 107.24, 'duration': 3.5}, {'text': 'the i newspaper reports that the total sales of the 
 Xbox 360 in Portugal was just under 40,000 units.', 'start': 110.911, 'duration': 6.839}, {'text': 'If we think of the 7800 Vodafone TV subscribers and the 
 nearly 40,000 owners of an Xbox 360 in Portugal,', 'start': 118.285, 'duration': 6.335}, {'text': ' it will be easy to conclude that the amount of people 
 who have both the service of Vodafone and an Xbox 360,', 'start': 124.958, 'duration': 7.072}, {'text': 'able to take advantage of this integration, would be minimal.', 'start': 132.032, 'duration': 3.708}, {'text': 'But the Xbox marketing in Portugal is full of surprises...', 'start': 136.269, 'duration': 4.201}, {'text': 'In February 2010, barely two months after the launch of this joint initiative,', 'start': 141.008, 'duration': 5.172}, {'text': 'Microsoft Portugal declares that 50% of Xbox users in Portugal 
 joined the service of Vodafone TV on Xbox 360.', 'start': 146.447, 'duration': 9.513}, {'text': '50%...!', 'start': 156.59, 'duration': 1.33}, {'text': 'It is known that in the first quarter of 
 2010, Vodafone raised its market share to 0.6%,', 'start': 164.197, 'duration': 5.743}, {'text': 'which represented at that time about 14,500 subscribers.', 'start': 170.27, 'duration': 3.27}, {'text': '50% of the total Xbox 360 users in Portugal corresponded 
 to 20,000 consoles at the end of 2009.', 'start': 173.541, 'duration': 7.209}, {'text': 'Even if all the subscribers of Vodafone TV 
 had an Xbox 360 in February 2010,', 'start': 180.915, 'duration': 5.105}, {'text': 'all together would not be even half of all Xbox users in Portugal.', 'start': 186.62, 'duration': 4.47}, {'text': 'As much pointless as it may seem, it must be asked:', 'start': 192.159, 'duration': 3.671}, {'text': 'How is that 50% of Xbox 360 users have joined the 
 Vodafone TV service from December 2009 to February 2010?', 'start': 196.363, 'duration': 9.577}, {'text': 'I confess that I struggle to keep up with this math ...', 'start': 206.307, 'duration': 3.833}, {'text': 'Fast-forward to Christmas 2010.', 'start': 210.745, 'duration': 1.995}, {'text': 'Once again, the campaigns return to stores in Portugal 
 and this time the foundation is Kinect,', 'start': 213.447, 'duration': 4.473}, {'text': "Microsoft's revolutionary camera, which allowed to play without controllers.", 'start': 218.251, 'duration': 3.739}, {'text': 'Among other features, Kinect also allows voice control,', 'start': 222.122, 'duration': 3.868}, {'text': 'used to navigate the interface in the console, 
 control movie playback, or search with Bing.', 'start': 226.226, 'duration': 5.474}, {'text': 'Portugal was left out of the pioneers with native voice in Kinect,', 'start': 232.165, 'duration': 3.935}, {'text': 'which in fact is not surprising when you consider that this console 
 is available for more than 6 years in our country', 'start': 236.103, 'duration': 5.807}, {'text': "and we still don’t have Portugal's Portuguese language in its operating system.", 'start': 241.909, 'duration': 3.471}, {'text': 'And once again consumers were misled when promoters and 
 even managers of the product in Portugal', 'start': 245.779, 'duration': 6.471}, {'text': ' predicted the arrival of Portuguese language for Kinect in 2011.', 'start': 252.252, 'duration': 4.508}, {'text': 'It seems legitimate to ask:', 'start': 256.923, 'duration': 1.937}, {'text': 'Where is support for Kinect in Portuguese?', 'start': 258.859, 'duration': 3.371}, {'text': 'This week marks the arrival of a new update to the Xbox 360,', 'start': 263.13, 'duration': 3.14}, {'text': 'which is not only renewing the presentation side of things, 
 as the very content available on the console.', 'start': 266.267, 'duration': 5.333}, {'text': 'It is the first step in turning the 
 Xbox into the living room TV portal,', 'start': 271.972, 'duration': 3.938}, {'text': 'through access to television channels and Internet services like YouTube and DailyMotion.', 'start': 275.909, 'duration': 4.801}, {'text': 'Portugal is for now off the list of contents to enter this first phase,', 'start': 281.214, 'duration': 3.506}, {'text': 'and a Microsoft representative has told Eurogamer Portugal, there are no 
 plans for them to be included in the future.', 'start': 285.285, 'duration': 6.475}, {'text': 'The official Microsoft site refers to our country a 
 peculiar exception - the Vodafone TV service.', 'start': 292.225, 'duration': 6.745}, {'text': 'And after all, if 50% of the players participated in 
 this service, we may not even need anything else...', 'start': 298.966, 'duration': 6.574}, {'text': "I'll recap the three questions I posed as a result of three 
 years of promises and more dubious statistics that many political speeches:", 'start': 307.441, 'duration': 7.069}, {'text': "Why didn't they release any Portuguese songs for Lips?", 'start': 315.182, 'duration': 3.338}, {'text': 'How is that 50% of Xbox 360 users have joined the 
 Vodafone TV service from December 2009 to February 2010?', 'start': 319.085, 'duration': 9.345}, {'text': 'Where is support for Kinect in Portuguese?', 'start': 329.296, 'duration': 2.974}, {'text': 'Pass the message and share this video so we can see 
 clarified, once and for all, these and other issues.', 'start': 333.334, 'duration': 8.076}]
